cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with medical image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new method for uncertainty estimation, which involves test-time augmentation and Monte Carlo simulation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with medical imaging (cs.MM) and proposes a new theoretical formulation for test-time augmentation, which involves modeling noise and image transformations, which is related to neural engineering (cs.NE).
